{
  "stem": "11089.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "My mother lit candles.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "We start blessing, naturally.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "It's a-- it was a [NON-ENGLISH], a yontiff.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the Shabbos, really, as they say, the Zohar says, that [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Which means, the sixth day of the weeks are taking in the spirit from one day.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That is Shabbos, spiritual.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's why we say today is the first day of Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Today [HEBREW] Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Every day you mention what?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because that gives you spirit.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, it's coming.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's coming.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's coming, The next Shabbos is coming.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So really, if you participate in such a Shabbos, you will wait to get ready for the next Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Especially, the village of the very poor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't see a piece of meat the whole week.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They didn't see a piece of white bread the whole week.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Shabbos came.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had a soup, a chicken soup.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And little piece of chicken meat.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Oy, it was a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I remember a man, Yosel the [NON-ENGLISH], Yosel the shoemaker.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He used to go-- I remember, once I was with him because-- because my parents used to-- every spoon, [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Every spoon with soup, used to say, it's [SPEAKING HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was the honor of Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was the Shabbos in our small village.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The villagers, what happened there, you know, they left according [NON-ENGLISH], because the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because the [NON-ENGLISH] lived in those hills, the Carpathian Hills, not far from us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the villagers took the idea of [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Means you don't have to know too much Talmud and Torah.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The meaning is the heart.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The heart.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "If your heart is close to God, you're closer to God than the one who knows-- who knows what, and he's not close to God.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
